datos.d<-ts_data[4:8]
names(datos.d)
## [1] "ts.1" "ts.2" "ts.3" "ts.4" "ts.5"
dim(datos.d)
## [1] 1430    5
attach(datos.d)
datos.ts<-ts(datos.d)
autoplot(datos.ts)

autoplot(datos.ts, facets = TRUE)

round(corr<-cor(datos.ts),2)
##      ts.1 ts.2 ts.3 ts.4 ts.5
## ts.1 1.00 0.96 0.95 0.92 0.91
## ts.2 0.96 1.00 0.94 0.96 0.87
## ts.3 0.95 0.94 1.00 0.90 0.91
## ts.4 0.92 0.96 0.90 1.00 0.81
## ts.5 0.91 0.87 0.91 0.81 1.00
corrplot(corr, method="circle")

y1<-datos.ts[,1]
y2<-datos.ts[,2]
y3<-datos.ts[,3]
y4<-datos.ts[,4]
y5<-datos.ts[,5]

Autocorrelation:

par(mfrow=c(2,3))
acf(y1,lag.max=400,ci=0.95)

location 1

par(mfrow=c(1,3))
ts.plot(y1)
acf(y1,lag.max=500,ci=0.95)
pacf(y1,lag.max=500,ci=0.95)

#diff 1
dy1<-diff(y1)

par(mfrow=c(1,3))
ts.plot(dy1)
acf(dy1,lag.max=500,ci=0.95)
pacf(dy1,lag.max=500,ci=0.95)

Spectral analysis

# Spectral Analysis
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
raw.spec1 <- spec.pgram(y1, taper = 0)
plot(raw.spec1, log = "no")

max(raw.spec1$spec)
## [1] 62741.95
(freq<-raw.spec1$freq[(raw.spec1$spec==max(raw.spec1$spec))])
## [1] 0.002777778
(periodo<-1/freq)
## [1] 360
ts.plot(datos.ts, col=1:9)
spec = mvspec(datos.ts, spans=c(3,3), taper=.1)
